# Apple VDM Implementation Walkthrough

I have implemented support for Apple-specific VDM commands (Reboot and DFU) on the STM32G071RB. These commands allow the Nucleo board to control the connected iPad/Apple device over USB Power Delivery.

## Changes Made

### VDM Layer
- **[usbpd_vdm_user.h](file:///Users/leon/code/usb-pd-vdm/USBPD/Target/usbpd_vdm_user.h)**: Added Apple SVID (0x05AC) and action IDs (0x105 for Reboot, 0x106 for DFU).
- **[usbpd_vdm_user.c](file:///Users/leon/code/usb-pd-vdm/USBPD/Target/usbpd_vdm_user.c)**:
  - Implemented [USBPD_VDM_SendAppleCommand](file:///Users/leon/code/usb-pd-vdm/USBPD/Target/usbpd_vdm_user.c#581-587) to initiate the VDM request.
  - Updated [USBPD_VDM_SendSpecific](file:///Users/leon/code/usb-pd-vdm/USBPD/Target/usbpd_vdm_user.c#448-479) to fill the correct VDOs (Action ID and Argument) when an Apple "Perform Action" command is requested.
  - Used `USBPD_SOPTYPE_SOP2_DEBUG` (SOP'' DEBUG) as required by Apple devices for these commands.

### Application Layer
- **[main.c](file:///Users/leon/code/usb-pd-vdm/Core/Src/main.c)**:
  - Added button polling logic in the default RTOS task.
  - **Short Press** (< 2s): Triggers an Apple Reboot command.
  - **Long Press** (> 2s): Triggers an Apple DFU command.

## Verification Steps

### 1. Build and Flash
Compile the project and flash it to your STM32G071RB Nucleo board.

### 2. Connect to iPad
Connect the iPad to the USB-C port of the SRC1M1 board. Monitor the serial output:
- You should see `[DPM] Port0: Explicit Contract -> VDM Discovery` once PD negotiation is complete.

### 3. Trigger Reboot
Press the User Button (Blue) briefly.
- Output: `Button: Short Press -> Apple Reboot`
- iPad should restart.

### 4. Trigger DFU
Press and hold the User Button (Blue) for more than 2 seconds.
- Output: `Button: Long Press -> Apple DFU`
- iPad should enter DFU mode.

> [!NOTE]
> The iPad may need to be in a state where it accepts these commands (e.g., connected as a UFP to the Nucleo acting as DFP/Source).
